 JOHANNEBSURG - The family of Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi says there are no signs that the 93-year-old is ready to relinquish his responsibilities and retire anytime soon. Doctors admitted him to hospital for routine blood tests and some much-needed rest. READ | Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi hospitalised The prince remains an active member of Parliament and serves as the Zulu Prime Minister. The family says they will issue an update upon Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi's discharge from the hospital.